.TH "nft_data_init" 9 "nft_data_init" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
nft_data_init \- parse nf_tables data netlink attributes
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" nft_data_init
.BI "(const struct nft_ctx *ctx "  ","
.BI "struct nft_data *data "  ","
.BI "unsigned int size "  ","
.BI "struct nft_data_desc *desc "  ","
.BI "const struct nlattr *nla "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "ctx" 12
context of the expression using the data
.IP "data" 12
destination struct nft_data
.IP "size" 12
maximum data length
.IP "desc" 12
data description
.IP "nla" 12
netlink attribute containing data

Parse the netlink data attributes and initialize a struct nft_data.
The type and length of data are returned in the data description.

The caller can indicate that it only wants to accept data of type
NFT_DATA_VALUE by passing NULL for the ctx argument.
